<P>
 27.10.1998   US-based PerSuaSiVe SoftWorX Registration Site
<P>

   As with 27 Oct 1998 PerSuaSiVe SoftWorX now is able to offer
   registration for US and canadian citizens directly at an
   US-based registration site, thanks to Jon Peterson.
<P>
   Registrations now can be directed as follows:
<P>
        (Rest of the World)       (USA, Canada)
<P>
   To:  Andreas R. Kleinert       Jon Peterson<BR>
        Sandstrasse 1             Attn: PerSuaSiVe SoftWorX<BR>
        D-57072 Siegen            PO Box 62472<BR>
        Germany                   San Angelo, TX 76906-2472<BR>
<P>

   Additionally, there's still our introductory offer for JPEG-Box
   running:
<P>
   Starting with 5 October 1998, PerSuaSiVe SoftWorX offers a special
   introductory freebie offer for their new tool "JPEG-Box" - limited
   until 31 December 1998.
<P>
   JPEG-Box completes the current set of "WWW datatypes" (akJFIF and akPNG)
   and WWW image creation programs (PNG-Box) by adding the missing
   complementary tool for akJFIF datatype.
<P>
   With JPEG-Box you can easily convert any source graphics as supported
   by datatypes or SuperView-Library into progressive or non-progressive
   JPEG (JFIF) graphic files for use on the WWW or otherwise. Of course
   with PPC support for faster image saving (in the registered version).
<P>
   Anyone who registers
<P>
<UL><LI>- anything from us via RegNet (see "RegNet-Offers" listing)
    <LI>  - any of the available "discount" Shareware bundles from us<BR>
        (see "Discount" offers listing) for more than 25 DM</UL>
<P>
   until 31 December 1998, additionally will receive a free keyfile
   for JPEG-Box as well.
<P>
   Of course JPEG-Box can be registered solely as well, using the
   included registration form.
<P>
<UL>
<LI> Registration details:   Aminet:docs/anno/SV-Discount.lha<
<LI> JPEG-Box:               Aminet:gfx/conv/JPEG-Box.lha      (soon)
<LI> More programs:          <A HREF="http://home.t-online.de/home/Andreas_Kleinert/support.htm">http://home.t-online.de/home/Andreas_Kleinert/support.htm</A>
<LI> WWW site:               <A HREF="http://wdo.de/ark/">http://wdo.de/ark/</A></UL>
<P>
